cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of measuring and bounding the concentration of a dataset, which is relevant to machine learning and computer vision tasks such as image classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the intrinsic robustness of image classification benchmarks, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
